==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*διακονέω / diakoneō / dee-ak-on-eh'-o

===Etymology===
*From [[διάκονος]] {{GG|1249}}; to be an attendant, that is, wait upon (menially or as a host, friend or [figuratively] teacher); technically to act as a Christian deacon: 

===Verb===
'''διακονέω'''

# (ad-) [[minister]] (unto), [[serve]], use the office of a [[deacon]].

